<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Ok, ome little tid bits here. After all the people shun us for groups. After everyone puts thier own greed above working togehter. We can make out like bandits down here.<P>how?<P>First, don't expect to power level. but if you want to spend some time making really nice loot and getting all your Seal gear fast, it is easier for us than anyone.<P>Half of everything down here is charmable, this is a great benefit. What I do to maximize it is grab a pet (at lev 29 I only had a lev 24 pet and it was fine) and start hunting blue and green MOBs. We can harvest emerald seals relatively easy, and since we can take 3 to 5 of these at once, we get decent group bonus. It is not fast, but at level 29 i was doing a bubble of XP an hour with no real risk.<P>Multiples comes into play even moreso on loot. When you get a multiple pull, the last MOB killed will drop a chest. This is the devious part...<P>I normally part myself at the top of a downward sloping section of the path. i can then pull Necyomancers and Familiars, and plated fields from the room "below" me. I amke sure there is a gorup hunting below me that could use my aid. One particular gorup never said thanks once, even though i hit every 4+ pull they had with a free AE mez. Didn't bother me though, because if they are not fast enough to kill the entire pull, the last one woudl break Mez and rush uphill to me. Again, this is the last of a group, and the larger the group pulled, the more coin in that chest! All teh thanks i needed. <P>Was it huge? no not really. but i was pulling in about 20 seals an hour, 1 bubble of XP, and over 10 gold. Not too shabby when you consider almost NO risk involved.<P>So what about after i have purchased all my emerald seal gear? Well, the greed of high levels helps us again. all of them want to twink their lower level characters with emerald gear. they can't harvest emeralds however. so if you have plenty, they will frequently trade you Saphires or diamond for emeralds, usually on a 1 to 1 exchange.<P>All this is self serving, and yet you seem to be the most kind and altrusitic person there, always ready with a casual mez to save someones ass. I never needed worry, as I always had free heals and buffs, for me and my pet.<P>It is actually a very cool social dynamic. everyone helping out for the greater good. I was honestly helping others, and they me. but the net gain... well... like I said, we get to be nice and loved AND make out like bandits.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...<P>Please visit our <A HREF="http://www.yesterdayland.com/popopedia/shows/toys/ty1050.php" TARGET=_blank>Sponsors!</A>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
