<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
There are lots of neat things about DF, but there also some problems as well.<P>My biggest problem is that with the concentration of mobs in DF, it is very very easy to get overwhelmed while trying to Mez.  First, it is very hard to target; we don't get the option of moving around to find a clear field of view as we can do outdoors.  Second, once you get the pulled mobs mezzed, you get jumped by 2 or 3 more from behind or the side or who knows where.  Third, sorcerers have THE hardest job of all the other casters.  Our primary ability requires a LOT of attention, and causes our death much more often than other classes.<P>I guess the root of the problem is that we can generate the aggro of a paladin but have the defensive of wet paper towels.  This has always been the case, but in DF the problem is magnified 10 fold.  I don't think we should get better armor or anything (I wish), but it would be great if the aggro of AE mez could be toned down some.  Or at the very least, let Protect work for mezzes.
</FONT>
